  • City: MIDDLETOWN

  • Hazmat Fatalities: 0
  • Hazmat Injuries: 0
  • Non-Hazmat Fatalities: 0
  • Total Amount Of Damages: 0
  • Serious Incident Ind: No
  • Description: PACKAGE WAS BROUGHT BACK TO DMP PROCESSING AREA IN SPILL TRAY. RESPONDER SAW WAS A PACKAGE WITH CORROSIVE 8 AND OXIDIZER 5.1 LABELS. READ DECISION TREE AND RESPONSE SHEETS FOR BOTH. ADDED SILVER SHIELD LINERS TO INSIDE OF GLOVES. SOLIDIFIED LIQUIDS WITH ZEP ZORBENT AND THEN TESTED WITH PH TAPE. WAS NOT WITHIN 6-9 RANGE SO ADDED SODIUM BICARBONATE TILL MIXTURE WAS NOT AN ALKALINE OR BASE. READ WASTE DISPOSAL CHART AND PROCESSED THROUGH THE DMP. AFTER PROCESSING, REFERRED TO DECONTAMINATION CHECKLIST.

item.description:

  • Incident Date: 2025-01-10
  • City: CARLISLE
  • State: PA
  • Report Type: A hazardous material incident
  • Mode Of Transportation: Highway
  • Carrier/Reporter: XPO LOGISTICS, LLC
  • Hazmat Fatalities: 0
  • Hazmat Injuries: 0
  • Non-Hazmat Fatalities: 0
  • Total Amount Of Damages: 0
  • Serious Incident Ind: No
  • Description: At 8:41 AM ET, BCA contacted the call center to report a spill that occurred on the dock in Carlisle, PA. The spill consists of approximately 2 cups of 1360 Urethane Reducer Fast, which released from 1–4-gallon plastic jug due to a forklift blade puncturing the container while it was inside of a cardboard box, dampening the box. No surfaces were affected by the spill. ERTS reviewed the SDS with the terminal, who stated they will place the box and the jug into a 20-gallon poly drum.
